Titulo: Low polarization resistance of Ni-Cu-Ce oxide anode synthesized by coprecipitation with tetramethylammonium carbonate for intermediate temperature SOFC

Sentencas: Ni-Cu-Ce oxide powders for intermediate temperature SOFC anodes were synthesized by coprecipitation using tetramethylammonium carbonate and decomposition of coprecipitated metal carbonates.
Titulo: Low polarization resistance of Ni-Cu-Ce oxide anode synthesized by coprecipitation with tetramethylammonium carbonate for intermediate temperature SOFC

Sentencas: The synthesized oxide powder was found to have a high surface area.
Titulo: Low polarization resistance of Ni-Cu-Ce oxide anode synthesized by coprecipitation with tetramethylammonium carbonate for intermediate temperature SOFC

Sentencas: A 30% Ni-30% Cu-40% Ce anode fired at a low temperature of 900 C on a Ce(0.9)Gd(0.1)O(1.95) electrolyte provided low electrode polarization with an estimate of less than 0.1 Omega cm(2) at temperatures over 600 degrees C on wet 50% H(2) despite the Ni-Cu metallic phase in the anode was only 30% by volume.
Titulo: Low polarization resistance of Ni-Cu-Ce oxide anode synthesized by coprecipitation with tetramethylammonium carbonate for intermediate temperature SOFC
